        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 2 at 6:43PM CDT by NWS San Angelo TX</headline>
        <description>At 642 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Eola, moving south at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Vancourt, Eola, Live Oak, and Vick.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
